  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "RNA virus of arenaviridae family\nEndemic to parts of West Africa\n100,000-300,000 infections every year\nAnimal vector:  Multimammate rat (\nMastomys natalensis\n)\nA type of\nviral hemorrhagic fever",
      "subsections": {
        "Transmission": {
          "text": "Infected Multimammate rats shed virus in urine and droppings\nInhalation, ingestion, or direct contact of excrement or soiled food\nDirect contact with bodily fluids of infected human",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "viral hemorrhagic fever",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Viral_hemorrhagic_fevers"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Transmission": {
      "text": "Infected Multimammate rats shed virus in urine and droppings\nInhalation, ingestion, or direct contact of excrement or soiled food\nDirect contact with bodily fluids of infected human",
      "subsections": {},
