    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "IgM or IgG ELISA or RT-PCR may be used to diagnose acute infections\nLymphopenia and elevated transaminases are non-specific, but may indicate worse prognosis",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Supportive care is the hallmark of management\nStrict isolation precautions: standard, contact and droplet\nLimit entry and maintain a log of people who enter the room\nRibavirin\nhas been shown to decrease mortality\nMost effective when given early (within 6 days)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Ribavirin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Ribavirin"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Admit (consider ICU admission)\nThose that seek medical care are more likely to have serious infections:\nHospital mortality rates can reach 25%\nOveral mortality rates are much less; around 5000 deaths per 100,000-300,000 infections annually",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
